  4.4 Comparative Discussion

  ┌───────────────────────┬──────────────────────┬──────────────────────┬───────────────────────────┐
  │        Aspect         │    Structured TF     │         VSM          │           BM25            │
  ├───────────────────────┼──────────────────────┼──────────────────────┼───────────────────────────┤
  │ IDF weighting         │ No                   │ Yes                  │ Yes                       │
  ├───────────────────────┼──────────────────────┼──────────────────────┼───────────────────────────┤
  │ TF saturation         │ No                   │ Partial (log)        │ Yes (hard ceiling)        │
  ├───────────────────────┼──────────────────────┼──────────────────────┼───────────────────────────┤
  │ Length normalisation  │ Implicit (÷doc_len)  │ Approximate (÷√len)  │ Explicit (B=0.75)         │
  ├───────────────────────┼──────────────────────┼──────────────────────┼───────────────────────────┤
  │ Best performing query │ Author/title lookups │ Multi-term queries   │ All query types           │
  ├───────────────────────┼──────────────────────┼──────────────────────┼───────────────────────────┤
  │ Weakest query         │ Common-word queries  │ Very short documents │ Requires parameter tuning │
  └───────────────────────┴──────────────────────┴──────────────────────┴───────────────────────────┘

  BM25 consistently outperforms the other two approaches across most queries due to its combination of IDF
  weighting, TF saturation, and explicit length normalisation. As Manning et al. [2009, §11.4.3, p. 232]
  note, BM25 represents the state of the art among bag-of-words retrieval functions. However, all three
  approaches share a fundamental limitation — as bag-of-words models, none capture word order or semantic
  meaning, limiting their performance on phrase-based queries such as query 1.

References: Manning et al., §8.1 (p. 151), §8.3 (p. 158–159), §8.4 (p. 162), §11.4.3 (p. 232), §2.2.2 (p.
   28).

